title><link>https://mas.to/@carnage4life/111807278075827490</link><description>The New York Times with a classic example of lies, damn lies and statistics showing a downward trend line for a stat that went from 30% to 38%. üòÇ&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/807/278/159/316/716/original/de2cc5d904a92415.jpeg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/807/278/159/316/716/original/de2cc5d904a92415.jpeg" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111807660088533382</guid><pubDate>Tue, 23 Jan 2024 22:38:20 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Carsen Stringer (she/her)</title><link>https://neuromatch.social/@computingnature/111807682824627947</link><description>Simultaneous, cortex-wide and cellular-resolution neuronal population dynamics reveal an *unbounded* scaling of dimensionality with neuron number&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2024.01.15.575721v1" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;24.01.15.575721v1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/dimensionality" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;dimensionality&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/807/682/936/266/174/original/8b938bd214c915ab.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/807/682/936/266/174/original/8b938bd214c915ab.jpg" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">